There has been a security scare at an AFL training ground in Melbourne after three razor blades were found on the field ahead of Hawthorn's final session before the  grand final.

The open razor blades were located by security staff as they combed the field at Waverly Park in Melbourne's south east before the Hawks players kicked off their training session on Thursday.

Forty staff members were forced to sweep the grounds for more blades just minutes before training was scheduled to start. 

